Grammy-award singer Wizkid has become one of the African artists to earn a whooping sum of $1million dollars(N600 million) to perform at a show. Wizkid, who was announced as one of the stars headlining the 2022 Rolling Loud music festival in September, confirmed this in a recent post on his Instagram story. He wrote “Afro nigga! $1 million to pop out”.   BBNaija’s Rico Swarvey says tattoos scare men from single…     Yvonne Nelson weighs in on why people get married     Regina Daniels gets two new tattoos   American rapper, Futura a performing act for the same show ,also confirmed he was paid $1 million in his recent post. Dubbed the largest hip-hop festival in the world, Rolling Loud holds from September 9-11. The festival, which usually takes place in the United States, will hold in Canada for the first time in history. The three-day festival will also be headlined by American hip-hop stars, Dave and Future, with Wizkid headlining the third day of the festival.